# Authorize HTTP layer errors (22000-22099)
E22000 = The request must use the application/x-www-form-urlencoded content type.
E22001 = The request method is not supported. Use GET or POST.
E22002 = Missing required parameters: { $fields }.
E22003 = Authentication is required for this client.
E22004 = No active session found for the requested account.
E22005 = This authorization interaction is no longer available.
